<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFB3CB394797714DFEA0F98B" blockId="22.[151,1437,1322,1781]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<materialsCitation id="3B5AAB29FFB3CB394797714DFEA4F98B" elevation="380" location="In" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sicilia">
Habitat: Crenophilous. Rheocrenes and low order streams, at low and middle altitudes, 
<quantity id="4CCA0C91FFB3CB3943CA714DFAADF9F3" box="[1178,1290,1539,1565]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="380.0" valueMax="740.0" valueMin="20.0">
<elevation id="001F4647FFB3CB3943CA714DFAADF9F3" box="[1178,1290,1539,1565]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="380.0" valueMax="740.0" valueMin="20.0">20-740 m</elevation>
</quantity>
. 
<location id="8EEDF7AFFFB3CB394244714DFA8CF9F3" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039B1062FFB3CB3947C7738DFCA8F91B:8EEDF7AFFFB3CB394244714DFA8CF9F3" box="[1300,1323,1539,1565]" name="In" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" stateProvince="Sicilia">In</location>
<collectingRegion id="49F66F96FFB3CB394263714DFAD2F9F3" box="[1331,1397,1539,1565]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, 50 % of the records from springs, mostly rheocrenes, furthermore in karstic streams, possibly at sites with groundwater influence
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFB3CB3947977121FCA8F91B" blockId="22.[151,1437,1322,1781]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Distribution: Central and Southern Europe. In 
<collectingRegion id="49F66F96FFB3CB3945867121FCB0F967" box="[726,791,1647,1673]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sicily</collectingRegion>
only in the Iblei mountains and a spring complex at SW base of Mount Etna - records under « 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFB3CB39456971DDFCE2F943" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[569,837,1683,1709]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fonticolus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFB3CB39456971DDFD0BF943" box="[569,684,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Atractides</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFB3CB39458771DDFCE2F943" box="[727,837,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">fonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from the Central South (Gerecke 1991) and streams in the Simeto catchment (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFB3CB3946E971F9FDECF93F" author="Ferrito, V." box="[441,587,1719,1745]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="33 - 56" refId="ref73982" refString="Ferrito, V. (1994) Les macroinvertebres benthiques de la riviere Simeto (Sicile) et de quelques-uns de ses affluents. Annales de Limnologie, 30 (1), 33 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / limn / 1994003" type="journal article" year="1994">Ferrito 1994</bibRefCitation>
, det. Gerecke) do not refer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFB3CB3944F171F9FB97F93F" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[929,1072,1719,1745]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fonticolus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFB3CB3944F171F9FB97F93F" box="[929,1072,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. fonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but to various different species – the material in question is revised in the present paper.
</paragraph>
